    warning: spoilers<br />
<br />
monster is probably one of the best mystery/thriller mangas to ever exist even though it starts slow the pay off is worth it. thats one of the reasons why the manga can be better than the anime. the story follow kenzo tenma the protagonist of monster a neuro surgeon or sum. so this tenma dude has two lives in his hands. a little boy who got shot in da head and sum mayor guy. well ofc they told em to save the little kid. only to know that kid became a handsome as fuck antagonist mass murderer called johan liebert. Knowing this was tenmas

          <span style="display: none;" id="review411293">
        fault he must track johan and kill him.. this is where the story of monster starts<br />
<br />
Why Johan Liebert Is The Best Antagonist<br />
<br />
Most people agree with me on this, i also agree with myself on this.The more the story continues the more we learn about johan and his personality, why he kills. how he kills and his past self. they also gives us clues from the picture book &quot;the nameless monster&quot;. i mean even da fucking nazis wanted him. there is also this special trait of him of making people kill themselves through johans psychological torture with just his words. very well written character if i do say so myself.the story of monster revolves more on johan than tenma. i mean tenma was aight but dang.. he planned everything all the murder and shit. mans a fucking monster.<br />
<br />
i forgot to mention his twin sister anna which also plays a big part in the story from johans past and why he got shot in da head.theres also roberto which is an ass and lunge which i started to approve of when i was about to finish monster. . naoki urusaw makes amazing villians like johan or friend from 20th century boys. one of my favourite quotes from monster was &quot;the only thing all humans are equal in is death&quot;. johan says this straight to tenmas face in the final part of monster. and we all know that hes a neuro surgeon. his job is saving lives as best as he can for him every life is equal. the question is if the life he saved seeks to wreak harm(joahn) . the question arises of how all life is truly deserved to be saved or not<br />
<br />
For You, All Lives Are Created Equal. That&#039;s Why I Came Back To Life. But You&#039;ve Finally Come To Realize It Now, Haven&#039;t You? Only One Thing Is Equal For All, And That Is Death.<br />
<br />
The Ending Of Monster<br />
<br />
tbh i thought the ending was rushed so my weak ass brain decided to watch analysis vids to understand how great the ending of monster was. and yes it was pretty much incredible. yes, the massacre at 511 kinderhelm. johan planned all the murder everything.. even his own death. HE WAS PLAYING THE FATE GAME its the game mentioned in the earlier chapters to see if hes truly chosen by fate. grimmer died. lunge died,roberto died.. etc hes going to see if everything goes according to plan like it always has and some miracle made him alive somehow or he would die its a W for both tbh since he wanted to suicide. he says the quote i mentioned right when tenma was gonna kill himand does the forehead pointing thingie. he only does that when hes sure hes gonna die iirc. but then mfing nina comes out to stop tenma from shooting so he actually had to threaten to shoot the kid so he could die. and the father of the kid took out his gun and shot the man W johan died or did he.. yea tenma saved him lol cuz he sticked with his beliefs that every life is equal.<br />
<br />
theres also a continuation in light novel called another monster which tells us he is living a peaceful life now i think<br />
<br />
the philosophy of monster and the question of life and death truly makes it a masterpiece still read/watched by people till this day..<br />
<br />
story: 10/10<br />
art: 8/10<br />
suspense: 10/10<br />
characters: 9/10<br />
enjoyment: 9/10 cuz it hard to understand at first had to reread it
        
